<div class="a2">To: <b>Roos_Girl</b></div>
<div class="b2">
    <p>Doubling down on the joke explaining?</p>
<p>My post, a true story, is a self-contained witticism. When the reader realizes the lesbian has named her dog Peter and yells to it in public, &#8220;Peter, come!&#8221;, the reader is supposed to laugh.</p>
<p>If you do not laugh, however, and feel the need to respond to a joke online, one appropriate way to do that is to type &#8220;LOL!&#8221;</p>

