<div class="a2">To: <b>twhitak</b></div>
<div class="b2">
    I have lived with cats most of my life, all indoor cats, all lived to advanced old age, and I can&#39;t recall a single case of bird victims or even feathered evidence.<br />The cats do get daily outdoor privileges under supervision, but the birds seem to have settled on a mutually beneficial schedule.<br />My cats never visit neighboring properties.<p>Perhaps they should concentrate on catching, spaying and releasing <i>some</i> cat owners.
